		{"id":"66fcf7b2e2d6c420","x":1300,"y":-280,"width":780,"height":1020,"color":"3","type":"text","text":"# Permanenting Route entries in Routing table\n\n```\n1. cd /etc/sysconfig/network-scripts/\n2. vim route-ens160\n\nNote --> we are creating the file name route-160. Here you can create any name but make it state with ğŸ‘‰ route- and anything\n\n3. 10.0.2.0/32 via 192.168.43.1 \nğŸ‘‰ğŸ‘‰ğŸ‘‰ This is the entry we need to do inside route-ens160\n\n4. nmcli connection reload\n5. systemctl restart NetworkManager\n```\n\n### For Debian machine \n\n```\n1. cd /etc/network/interfaces\n\nğŸ‘‰ğŸ‘‰ This is the path where you will be creating file and do the entry\n```\n\n# Important --> \nWhere these information comes from meaning the information which we see in routing table where does it come from\n\n```\n1. cat /proc/net/route\nğŸ‘‰ğŸ‘‰ These file holds the information about IPV4\n\n2. cat /proc/net/ipv6_route\nğŸ‘‰ğŸ‘‰ THese file holds the information about IPV6\n\n3. cat /proc/net/rt_cache\nğŸ‘‰ğŸ‘‰ These file holds the cache related information\n```"}
